<li id="cite_note-101"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Pluto_(mythology)#cite_ref-101">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">P.G. Maxwell-Stuart, <i>Studies in Greek Colour Terminology: ΓΛΑΥΚΟΣ</i> (Brill, 1981), vol. 1, pp. 40, 42, citing Cornutus, <i>Theologiae Graecae Compendium</i> 9, 20, 35. The word γλαυκότης <i>(glaukotēs)</i>, however, is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Textual_criticism" title="Textual criticism">textual crux</a> in the passage pertaining to Pluto.</span>
