<li id="cite_note-120"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Pluto_(mythology)#cite_ref-120">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The nymph <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minthe" title="Minthe">Minthē</a>, a rival for the attentions of <i>Hades</i> (not named as Pluto), was transformed by Persephone into the mint plant, a major ingredient in the ritual drink of the mysteries (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strabo" title="Strabo">Strabo</a> 8.3.14).</span>
