<li id="cite_note-221"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Pluto_(mythology)#cite_ref-221">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Pirrotta, <i>Music and Theatre from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poliziano" title="Poliziano">Poliziano</a> to Monteverdi</i>, with <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=rDTeG7IG8jIC&amp;pg=PA274-IA6&amp;dq=Pluto+%22rotating+stage+and+the+interior+of+Hades%22+-fabula&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=QlVxTYy9NJLegQeLpMg7&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&amp;q=Pluto%20%22rotating%20stage%20and%20the%20interior%20of%20Hades%22%20-fabula&amp;f=false">Leonardo's drawing</a> (n.p.); Carlo Pedretti, <i>Leonardo: The Machines</i> (Giunti, 1999), p. 72.</span>
